<div class="container-fluid mt-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            <div class="card border-0 text-center animate__animated animate__fadeIn">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="card-title">About This Project...</h2>
                    <p class="card-text" style="text-align: justify;">This project is a comprehensive Library Management System developed using ASP.NET. It incorporates three pivotal tables: User, Book, and Borrower. Through meticulous database design and implementation, this system excels at Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) operations. The synergy between the User and Book tables is seamlessly integrated with the Borrower table, allowing for a dynamic interplay of data. This enables the system to track the incoming and outgoing flow of books, attributing each transaction to a specific user. The Borrow Date and Return Date fields serve as temporal markers, ensuring efficient management of due dates. A standout feature is the Universal Search Bar, an intuitive tool that enhances user experience. By selecting from a dropdown menu, users can opt to search by username, book name, or borrowing date. This innovative functionality empowers users to swiftly retrieve information tailored to their specific queries, whether it's a list of books borrowed by a particular user, details about a book's borrowers, or a user's borrowing history based on dates. This project exemplifies the seamless integration of technology and library management, offering an efficient and user-friendly solution for modern libraries.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

